Four people died in Johannesburg in the early hours of Sunday morning in a horrific accident in which three motor vehicles collided on the M1 south near the Marlboro off-ramp.At about 1.05am on Sunday the police and the emergency services responded to a call of a collision on the M1 road near the Marlboro off-ramp.Emergency services ascertained that two people had died on the scene, two were critically injured, while three escaped with moderate injuries.The two critically injured passengers had to be placed on ventilators by the advanced life support paramedics, but both died soon after arriving at the hospital. The police are investigating the circumstances leading to the accident .-TNA Reporter &nbsp;